REpresentational State Transfer

What is REST?
=============

What is State?
--------------

   state definition: goes here

- information that can change depending on when it is retrieved 

key points
- can be changed through interaction
- data held in an object
- tie together physical and programmatic examples
- state is relative to the subject
   - the system as a whole
   - a collection
   - a single entity
   - a property of an entity

Examples
- properties of an object
- human state
- state of a machine

What is a Representation
------------------------

   representation definition: goes here

key points
- a way to describe state in different ways

- representations in code
- code is not portable (bound to that runtime)
- TIP: formats (MIME types)
   - support use case of consumer
   - HTML, plain text, XML, JSON, images, binary
   - for broader applicability (let consumer define presentation) use more generic representation
- generic representation
   - balance between language-agnostic, processing efficiency and structure
   - JSON provides all 3

